author: Jack Davis
title: Hillary Clinton Joins Her SNL Double For Dinner
text:
Hillary Clinton Joins Her SNL Double For Dinner ... took a thinly veiled shot ... by Jack Davis February 17, 2017 at 11:05am Share on Facebook 240 Tweet Email Email Print Advertisement - story continues below 
Former Democratic presidential nominee Hillary Clinton was in the news this week after she was spotted at a New York City restaurant having diner with Kate McKinnon, the actress who played Clinton on Saturday Night Live . 
Clinton and McKinnon had dinner at Orso restaurant where, according to the New York Post’s Page Six , “(l)ots of laughter emanated from their table.” . @HillaryClinton and Kate McKinnon (SNL's Hillary) enjoy a night on the town in NYC: https://t.co/OKs5PnYQH0 pic.twitter.com/4FwFlFyNbk 
— Marlow Stern (@MarlowNYC) February 17, 2017 Advertisement - story continues below Pro-Trump Singer Hopes To Bring Joy To The White House 
Clinton was on her way to see Glenn Close in the show Sunset Boulevard . 
Page Six reported that while Clinton and McKinnon dined, one fellow diner adapted President Donald Trump’s campaign rally riff and called out, “Lock him up.” 
Some on Twitter were less than thrilled. @MarlowNYC @HillaryClinton Spotted: a loser, her body double and a minion. 2nd bottle of wine & it Looks like a bad Cheers episode. ♪♪♪ “You wanna go where everybody Thinks you Won” ♪♪♪ 
— Michael Zietlow (@mzguru) February 17, 2017 @MarlowNYC @thedailybeast @HillaryClinton are you still raising money from Middle East despots? 
— Bassey Mfon (@ak_bassque) February 17, 2017 Advertisement - story continues below 
Clinton, who was not in the limelight in the weeks after Trump defeated her for the White House, has been making more appearances of late. 
On Thursday, she took a thinly veiled shot at Trump while attending an event at which the U.S. Postal Service unveiled stamps featuring designer Oscar de la Renta. 
“Oscar de la Renta was an immigrant,” Clinton said at Grand Central Terminal. 
“What a fitting person to be chosen by our Postal Service, mentioned, by the way, in the Constitution, something we should all read and reread in today’s times … Let there be many, many more immigrants with the love of America that (he) exemplified every single day.” Advertisement - story continues below
